dc_description_s: This data represents lakes less than 50 acres Wisconsin in 2019. [These lakes are PriorityNavigable Waters under the State of Wisconsin's Waterways Protection Program. Priority Navigable Waterways include lakes less than 50 acres, waters with self-sustaining musky, sturgeon and walleye populations, tributaries to and rivers connecting naturally reproducing populations, and perennial tributaries to trout streams.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most current data, please visit: [https://data-wi-dnr.opendata.arcgis.com/]
